subsection.def:
employee (僱員) means
                an employee to whom, by virtue of section 4, this Ordinance
                applies;

paragraph.content:
attributable to a contribution made to such a scheme by the employer;
                            (Added 4 of 2022 s.
                            3)

subsection.def:
holiday pay (假日薪酬) means the holiday pay provided for by section 40;
                    (Added 39 of 1973 s.
                2)

paternity leave (侍產假) means the paternity leave provided for in Part IIIA;
                    (Added 21 of 2014 s.
                3)

paragraph.content:
where the employee’s contract of employment is terminated by notice in
                        accordance with section 6, the date on which that notice
                        expires;

where the employee’s contract of employment is terminated by payment in
                        lieu of notice in accordance with section 7, the date up to which
                        such wages are calculated;

where the employee terminates his contract of employment without notice
                        or payment in lieu in accordance with section 10, the date on
                        which termination takes effect;

where a continuous contract of employment specifies an age of
                        retirement and the employee retires at that age, the date of
                        retirement;

recognized by the employer as part of the employee’s wages;
                            (Added 48 of 1984 s.
                            2)

subsection.def:
wage period (工資期)
                means the period in respect of which wages are payable under a contract of
                employment or under section 22;

paragraph.content:
any travelling allowance which is of a non-recurrent nature;
                            (Added 74 of 1997 s.
                            3)

subparagraph.content:
in any other case, the date on which paternity leave is taken;
                        (Added 21 of 2014 s.
                        3)

where the employee’s contract of employment is terminated by payment in
                    lieu of notice in accordance with section 7, the date on which the
                    termination takes effect;

paragraph.content:
the right to be or to become a member or an officer of a trade union
                    registered under the Trade Unions Ordinance (Cap.
                        332);

where he is a member or an officer of any such trade union, the right, at
                    any appropriate time, to take part in the activities of the trade
                    union;

prevents or deters, or does any act calculated to prevent or deter, an
                    employee from exercising any of the rights conferred on him by subsection (1);
                    or

is a time within his working hours at which, in accordance with
                        arrangements agreed with or consent given by or on behalf of his employer,
                        it is permissible for him to take part in those activities;

subparagraph.content:
because of the operation of the employee’s contract of employment, one
                        or more gratuities based on length of service have been paid to the
                        employee;

because of the operation of the employee’s contract of employment, the
                        employee becomes entitled to payment of one or more gratuities based on
                        length of service;

because of the operation of that contract, the employee becomes
                        entitled to payment of one or more employer-funded (specified) ORS
                        benefits;

one or more employer-funded (voluntary) MPFS benefits are being held in
                        one or more mandatory provident fund schemes in respect of the employee;
                        and

because of the operation of the employee’s contract of employment, one
                        or more gratuities based on length of service have been paid to the
                        employee;

because of the operation of the employee’s contract of employment, the
                        employee becomes entitled to payment of one or more gratuities based on
                        length of service;

because of the operation of that contract, the employee becomes
                        entitled to payment of one or more employer-funded (specified) ORS
                        benefits;

one or more employer-funded (voluntary) MPFS benefits are being held in
                        one or more mandatory provident fund schemes in respect of the employee;
                        and

because of the operation of the employee’s contract of employment, one
                        or more gratuities based on length of service have been paid to the person
                        in respect of the employee;

because of the operation of that contract, one or more employer-funded
                        (specified) ORS benefits have been paid to the person in respect of the
                        employee;

as a result of the death, the person, because of the operation of the
                        employee’s contract of employment, becomes entitled to payment of one or
                        more gratuities based on length of service;

as a result of the death, the person, because of the operation of that
                        contract, becomes entitled to payment of one or more employer-funded
                        (specified) ORS benefits;

paragraph.content:
as a result of the death, the employer is required to pay a long service
                    payment under section 31RA to a person (Person A);
                    and

subparagraph.content:
as a result of the death, Person B, because of the operation of the
                        employee’s contract of employment, becomes entitled to payment of one or
                        more gratuities based on length of service;

as a result of the death, Person B, because of the operation of that
                        contract, becomes entitled to payment of one or more employer-funded
                        (specified) ORS benefits;

as a result of the employee’s death, the administrator of an
                        occupational retirement scheme has paid an employer-funded (specified) ORS
                        benefit to Person B;

paragraph.content:
if the employee is subject to a Cap. 599
                    requirement due to the employee’s serious and wilful misconduct;
                        (Added 5 of 2022 s. 7)

subparagraph.content:
a certificate issued by the registered medical practitioner,
                                registered Chinese medicine practitioner or registered dentist
                                engaged by the employer for the purposes of the scheme;

(if the scheme does not cover medical treatment given by a
                                registered medical practitioner) a certificate issued by any
                                registered medical practitioner;

(if the scheme does not cover medical treatment given by a
                                registered Chinese medicine practitioner) a certificate issued by
                                any registered Chinese medicine practitioner;

(if the scheme does not cover medical treatment given by a
                                registered dentist) a certificate issued by any registered dentist;
                                or

paragraph.content:
the employee chooses to be examined by a registered medical practitioner
                    and no registered medical practitioner is engaged by the employer for the
                    purposes of the scheme;

if the employee’s pre-transition employment period is not less than 12
                        months—the period of 12 months immediately preceding the transition date;
                        or

subparagraph.content:
if the employee’s pre-transition employment period covers not
                                less than 30 normal working days—that employment period;
                                or

subsection.def:
pre-transition employment period
                    (轉制前僱傭期) has the meaning given by
                    section 1(1) of Schedule 11;

subparagraph.content:
has, within the preceding 5 years, been convicted of an offence against
                        the person of a child, young person or woman or of an offence involving
                        membership of a triad society, fraud, dishonesty or extortion;

has knowingly furnished to the Commissioner any false or misleading
                        information in connection with his application for the issue or renewal of
                        the licence;

has contravened any provision of this Part or any regulation made under
                            section 62;
                        (Amended 8 of 2018 s. 5)

has, within the preceding 5 years, been convicted of an offence against
                        the person of a child, young person or woman or of an offence involving
                        membership of a triad society, fraud, dishonesty or extortion;

paragraph.content:
requiring a licensee and the holder of a certificate of exemption to display
                his licence or certificate of exemption conspicuously at the place of business of
                the employment agency;

section.def:
lock-out (閉廠)
                and strike (罷工), respectively, have
                the meanings assigned to them in the Trade Unions Ordinance (Cap. 332);

paragraph.content:
that the employer, if apprehended or brought before a District
                            Judge under paragraph 3, or committed to prison under
                                paragraph 7, be released;

that no proceedings have been brought within 14 days after the
                            application under section 67 to recover any part of the debt
                            from the employer;

subparagraph.content:
the amount of the pre-transition portion of the payment is to
                                be reduced to an amount equivalent to the applicable ceiling;
                                and

because of the operation of the employee’s contract of
                                employment, one or more gratuities based on length of service have
                                been paid to the employee;

because of the operation of that contract, one or more
                                employer-funded ORS benefits have been paid to the
                                employee;

paragraph.content:
every one of the employer-funded ORS benefits referred to in
                            subsection (1)(b)(ii) that are employer-funded (specified)
                            ORS benefits;

every one of the employer-funded MPFS benefits referred to in
                            subsection (1)(b)(iii) that are employer-funded (voluntary)
                            MPFS benefits;

every one of the employer-funded ORS benefits referred to in
                            subsection (1)(b)(ii) that are employer-funded (basic
                            portion) exempt ORS benefits;

